The paper discusses limitations on steganography, which involves hiding secret information within covertexts. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the Kolmogorov complexity, which is a concept from computational complexity theory (cs.DS) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the speed of transmission of secret information, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
